org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client

Class MqttDisconnectResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.client.MqttDisconnectResponse

  • public class MqttDisconnectResponse
extends Object
    This Object holds relevant properties for the client to use once the TCP connection has either been lost, or if the server has gracefully disconnected.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MqttDisconnectResponse

        public MqttDisconnectResponse(org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.MqttException exception)
        Initialises a new MqttDisconnectResponse with an exception. This will only be thrown in the event of a non-clean disconnect, i.e. connection lost.
        Parameters:
        exception - The exception thrown containing details about the lost connection.

      • MqttDisconnectResponse

        public MqttDisconnectResponse(int returnCode,
                              String reasonString,
                              ArrayList<org.eclipse.paho.mqttv5.common.packet.UserProperty> userProperties,
                              String serverReference)
        Initialise a new MqttDisconnectResponse with parameters provided in an MqttDisconnect packet. This will be used when a clean disconnect has Occurred.
        Parameters:
        returnCode - The Disconnect Return Code
        reasonString - The Disconnect Reason String
        userProperties - The Disconnect User Properties
        serverReference - The Server Reference
